<subSubSection id="02C66578FFE2FFA3FF3D9F43684F7E9D" pageId="15" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFE2FFA3FF3D9F436BC87E3F" blockId="15.[151,756,775,1020]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE2FFA3FF3D9F4368057E7E" bold="true" box="[151,264,775,799]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species is characterized by an elongate test, usually reaching the maximum width very early in development. The sutures are distinct but not raised.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFE2FFA3FF3D9F21684F7E9D" blockId="15.[151,756,775,1020]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE2FFA3FF3D9F2168C57E1C" bold="true" box="[151,456,869,893]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
This species was originally described from the Chapapote Formation (Eocene) of 
<collectingCountry id="32CB7663FFE2FFA3FF3D9FE069E17EDD" box="[151,236,932,956]" name="Mexico" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. In the study area, it is recorded in the Paleocene 
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE2FFA3FF3D9F8069927EBD" box="[151,159,964,988]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">(</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFE2FFA3FF359F806B157EBD" authority="Zone" authorityName="Zone" box="[159,536,964,988]" class="Globothalamea" family="Truncorotaloididae" genus="Morozovella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="15" pageNumber="29" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="trinidadensis">
